On the first day of my internship, I attended a meeting with my supervisor in the laboratory to discuss
and plan the project that would be carried out throughout the internship. During the meeting, several 
project ideas were evaluated, the hardware and software technologies to be used were discussed, and 
the overall scope of the project was determined. After the evaluation process, it was decided to
develop a camera-based Virtual Piano system using the ESP32-CAM development board.

The primary objective of the project is to enable users to produce musical notes corresponding to
virtual piano keys by detecting hand movements through a camera, eliminating the need for a physical
piano keyboard. During the meeting, my supervisor explained that the project would not be limited to 
piano sounds only. In the later stages of development, sounds from different musical instruments will
also be integrated into the system. This approach aims to create a more comprehensive and interactive 
musical application that allows users to select and play different instrument sounds.

It was also planned to enhance the project by incorporating machine learning techniques in future
stages. In this context, image processing methods will be combined with machine learning algorithms 
to improve the accuracy of hand gesture detection. This approach is expected to increase the overall
performance of the system and enable it to adapt to different usage scenarios more effectively.

As a preparation for the project development process, my supervisor asked me to study the Canny 
edge detection algorithm, which is one of the most widely used algorithms in the field of image 
processing.

At the end of the day, the project topic was finalized, the main hardware and software technologies
were identified, and a development roadmap was established. In addition, the Canny edge detection 
algorithm was selected as the first research topic, providing a solid foundation for the image 
processing tasks that will be carried out in the following stages of the internship.
